- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is also likely because the paper discusses the history and generalizations of different types of logic. 
- cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) is relevant because the paper discusses different types of n-symbol or numerical valued logic. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is possible because the paper mentions applications of neutrosophic logic to physics, which could include control systems. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is less likely but still possible because the paper discusses the definition of neutrosophic norm and conorm, which could be relevant to programming languages that use non-classical logic.
